T1  - ISPAD Clinical Practice Consensus Guidelines 2022: Type 2 diabetes in children and adolescents
A1  - Shah A.S.
A1  - Zeitler P.S.
A1  - Wong J.
A1  - Pena A.S.
A1  - Wicklow B.
A1  - Arslanian S.
A1  - Chang N.
A1  - Fu J.
A1  - Dabadghao P.
A1  - Pinhas-Hamiel O.
A1  - Urakami T.
A1  - Craig M.E. 
AO  - Shah, Amy S.; ORCID: https://orcid.org/0000-0001-7297-139X
AO  - Zeitler, Philip S.; ORCID: https://orcid.org/0000-0001-5756-7858
AO  - Pena, Alexia S.; ORCID: https://orcid.org/0000-0002-6834-4876
AO  - Wicklow, Brandy; ORCID: https://orcid.org/0000-0002-6080-0494
AO  - Arslanian, Silva; ORCID: https://orcid.org/0000-0002-1528-9324
AO  - Dabadghao, Preeti; ORCID: https://orcid.org/0000-0003-0395-7812
AO  - Pinhas-Hamiel, Orit; ORCID: https://orcid.org/0000-0001-8365-8091
AO  - Urakami, Tatsuhiko; ORCID: https://orcid.org/0000-0001-7976-9557
AO  - Craig, Maria E.; ORCID: https://orcid.org/0000-0001-6004-576X
Y1  - 2022//
N2  - Since the 2018 ISPAD guidelines on this topic, follow-up of large cohorts from around the globe have continued informing the current incidence and prevalence of co-morbidities and complications in young adults with youth-onset type 2 diabetes (T2D). This chapter focuses on the risk factors, diagnosis and presentation of youth-onset T2D, the initial and subsequent management of youth-onset T2D, and management of co-morbidities and complications. We include key updates from the observational phase of the multi-center Treatment Options for Type 2 Diabetes in Adolescents and Youth (TODAY) clinical trial, the SEARCH for Diabetes in Youth (SEARCH) study and new data from the Restoring Insulin Secretion (RISE) study, a head-to-head comparison of youth onset vs adult-onset T2D. We also include an expanded section on risk factors associated with T2D, algorithms and tables for treatment, management, and assessment of co-morbidities and complications, and sections on recently approved pharmacologic therapies for the treatment of youth-onset T2D, social determinants of health, and settings of care given COVID-19 pandemic.Copyright © 2022 John Wiley & Sons A/S. Published by John Wiley & Sons Ltd.
