T1  - Genetic risk score to improve prediction and treatment in gestational diabetes mellitus
A1  - Tian Y.
A1  - Li P. 
Y1  - 2022//
N2  - Diabetes mellitus is a chronic disease caused by the interaction of genetics and the environment that can lead to chronic damage to many organ systems. Genome-wide association studies have identified accumulating single-nucleotide polymorphisms related to type 2 diabetes mellitus and gestational diabetes mellitus. Genetic risk score (GRS) has been utilized to evaluate the incidence risk to improve prediction and optimize treatments. This article reviews the research progress in the use of the GRS in diabetes mellitus in recent years and discusses future prospects.Copyright © 2022 Tian and Li.
