174. 
TY  - JOUR
DB  - Embase
AN  - 635120353
T1  - Health risks, etiology, diagnosis and treatment of insulin resistance
T3  - 28th European Congress on Obesity, ECO 2021. Online.
A1  - Govers E.
A1  - Schweitzer D.H.
A1  - Visscher T.L.
A1  - Wiggers I. 
Y1  - 2021//
N2  - Introduction: IR has been linked to central obesity, T2DM and cardio vascular risk factors. Yet, it is not treated as the cause of health problems. We aimed to further explore the role of IR on health and disease, its etiology, diagnostic tools and treatment. Method(s): We conducted an explorative review in Pubmed and Google Scolar on reviews and meta analyses on insulin resistance, related diseases, etiology, diagnostic tools and treatment. Result(s): Insulin resistance (IR) is the underlying health problem in overweight and obesity, T2DM, CVD, PCOS, several cancers, NAFLD, cirrhosis, skin diseases, depression, anxiety disorder, rheumatic arthritis, Chron's and Alzheimer's disease. It is seldom diagnosed in clinical and primary care, caused by high fat, high carbohydrate diet. Best detection by McAuley equasion, mandatory to prevent disease. Management should focus on restoring insulin sensitivity through loss of visceral fat by low carb, high protein diet, with special attention for fiber, omega 6-3 axis, gut health, unprocessed foods and the role of fructose, coffee, tea and alcohol. Behavioral aspects and exercise are also taken into consideration. Conclusion(s): Early recognition of IR in patients may help prevent the emergence of comorbidities and serious illness at a moment that they are still reversable.
